article.story: Grant Huffman's 23 points helped Davidson defeat Saint Louis 84-61 on Wednesday night. Huffman had five assists for the Wildcats (12-7, 2-4 Atlantic 10 Conference). Angelo Brizzi scored 15 points and added five assists. Reed Bailey finished 5 of 11 from the field to finish with 12 points. Bradley Ezewiro led the Billikens (8-11, 1-5) in scoring, finishing with 20 points and six rebounds. Terrence Hargrove Jr. added 14 points and six rebounds for Saint Louis. Sincere Parker finished with 10 points and six rebounds. Huffman scored 11 points in the first half and Davidson went into the break trailing 31-28. Brizzi's 15-point second half helped Davidson close out the 23-point victory. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
